Tried something new… and I liked it! 🏃‍♀️

I had never considered myself much of a runner, didn’t even like it, never got that “runners high”, so I had never done a race before. 

But I’ve hit a point in my life where when I don’t like something or don’t want to try something new… I accept this as a challenge! Because you really can’t judge something when you’ve never even tried it. So I went for it! Started the training and now that my first race is complete… I wanna do another! 

Which given the circumstances of this race, I even surprised myself. Waking up at 4am, standing in the freezing cold rain soaked to the bone, in a crowd of strangers by myself shivering, that when it dawned on me… I can’t wait to run! 

Running through the streets of brooklyn, the people who came out to support, the bands cheering us on. It was truly a fun experience! Then the hills started, I had not expected so many hills … to be honest my mantra was “you got this, fuck these hills, don’t let them slow you down” over and over until I made it to the finish line. 

Besides some soreness in my hips and knees, I felt great! So here’s to a new sport that I never thought I’d like 👊🏼

“A goal is just an awesome way to force growth on yourself” – Deena Kastor 🏃‍♀️

2023 🎖️ The year of my first triathlon.
Which led to my first half marathon
…which then led to more running and now qualifying for the nyc marathon 2024🏃‍♀️💨

A few key take aways from 2023…
👊🏼Cross training is the key 
🦾You will MAKE the time if it matters 
❤️ My support team has taken me further than I ever could alone 
😓 Don’t stop doing the hard things! 
For 6 months I took swim lessons and swam 3xs a week hating every second of it. All year I ran races and only now at the end am I sort of/kinda liking it. I chose these perfomance goals to challenge myself. To strengthen my discipline and confidence in myself. To learn, to grow and most importantly to keep myself healthy.  To know that I can come out the other side accomplished, not because it was easy. 

Closing this chapter proud & grateful. 
Excited for 2024🎉🎉🎉
